<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-06-09T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-06-09T07:00:00-05:00" n="354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5034: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-06-09T20:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">June 9,
                                        1923—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 9—1:12
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>211. My 210, June 9, 2 p.m. Strike ended. Reasons obscure. No change in
                            Peking. Koo has just informed me that he has requested President to drop
                            his name from further consideration for premiership.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>